A pupil died on Friday in a fire at Infill Academy in Komarock, Nairobi.The fire started in the upper section of a dormitory and spread to other areas.Nairobi police commander Japheth Koome said they were unable to put it out and save the six year-old."We are yet to establish the cause of the fire," he said.The incident comes days after 122 students were left in the cold after a dormitory was razed at Koimbi Boys' High School in Murang'a.Principal John Muthee said they suspected the fire, which completely destroyed the facility, resulted from an electric fault.Read: List of more than 100 schools affected in June, July arson attacksAlso read: Dialogue instead of burning schools, Uhuru tells students